+- **Safety:** `freeBoards` is changed only while holding `mutex`, so no two groups can be assigned the same whiteboard(s).
+- **Deadlock freedom:** no group holds one whiteboard while waiting for more; a group either waits outside `EnterRoom` or, once admitted, already has all `count` whiteboards.
+- **Starvation freedom:** requests wait in FIFO order, so later groups cannot pass earlier groups indefinitely.
+- **Concurrency:** `TryToAdmit()` keeps admitting waiting groups from the front of the queue as long as enough boards remain, so if several waiting groups can all fit, they are all released and may work concurrently in the room.
+- The algorithm uses only semaphores (`mutex` and the `gate[t]` semaphores).
